# Internationalization (i18n)

All user-facing messages MUST be translated.

## Usage

```typescript
import { translate } from '../../helpers/i18n.helper';

// ✅ GOOD - Translated message
message: translate(this.i18n, 'auth.login.success', request.language)

// ✅ GOOD - With variables
message: translate(this.i18n, 'auth.welcome', request.language, { name: user.name })

// ❌ BAD - Hardcoded message
message: 'Login successful'
```

## Translation Files

Location: `src/i18n/{language}/{domain}.json`

```
i18n/
├── en/
│   ├── auth.json
│   ├── common.json
│   ├── validation.json
│   └── errors.json
└── fr/
    ├── auth.json
    └── ...
```

## Validation Messages

```typescript
const schema = Joi.object({
  email: Joi.string()
    .email()
    .required()
    .messages({
      'any.required': translate(this.i18n, 'validation.email.required', data.language),
      'string.email': translate(this.i18n, 'validation.email.invalid', data.language),
    }),
});
```

## Rules

- Never hardcode user-facing strings
- Always pass `language` from request context
- Add new keys to both `en/` and `fr/` folders
